JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Civic Organisation (Sanco) condemned the ruthless killing of an ANC ward councillor in Richmond in KwaZulu-Natal and called on law enforcement agencies to leave no stone unturned until those responsible for a spate of murders in the area were behind bars. Sfiso Mkhize was shot dead in the violence-ravaged region on Thursday night, the third political figure killed there in the past few months.Deputy mayor Thandazile Phoswa was killed in April while municipal manager S bu Sithole was shot dead a month before. The ruthless political killings, senseless violence, and heinous crimes committed against elected public representatives undermine the notion of representative governance critical for delivery of services to our communities, Sanco national spokesman Jabu Mahlangu said on Saturday.READ: DA councillor shot dead in Cape TownHe conveyed Sanco s condolences to the Mkhize family and the ANC.Mahlangu urged the community to assist the police with the investigation into the killing, which he described as an act of cowardice aimed at undermining democratic governance. We call on our communities to protect their councillors against opportunistic political thuggery and the senseless violence. READ: Hawks take over Richmond political killings investigationMahlangu questioned the effectiveness of the multi-disciplinary task team appointed to tackle what appeared to be well-planned political assassinations. It needs to speedily get to the bottom of the spate of killings and establish whether there is a third force rekindling political rivalry in order to destabilise and throw the area into violent conflict, Mahlangu said. eNCA